ifconfig            - network interface configuration, used to view and change config params of our system
(networksetup -listallhardwareports - show allhardware to device to ethernet address mappings)
ping                - checks if a service is alive and also shows packet loss
nmap                - scans a network for open ports
netstat             - network statistics  
arp                 - address resolution and control
traceroute          - print the route packets take to network host
nslookup            - query Internet name servers interactively
dig                 - query DNS servers (https://www.madboa.com/geek/dig/)
whois               - query internet domain names ans network number directory service

ssh                 - secure shell for connecting to remote machines
scp                 - secure file transfer
